Freddie's primary learning mechanism is gm rs-learn, in-process, via src/learn/gm-learn.js (exports memorize/recall/autoRecall/prune/projectNamespace, lazy createPlugkit() singleton, graceful no-op degrade). The local-SQLite memory store is removed; the 9 third-party memory providers (plugins/memory-*/) are legacy opt-in only (src/cli/memory_setup.js DEFAULT_PROVIDER='gm'). The learning workflow: src/agent/machine.js runTurn auto-recalls salient memories for the prompt on turn entry (injected as a 'Relevant memories (gm rs-learn)' system part) and autoLearnTurn auto-memorizes a deduped 'Q:..A:..' salient fact on substantive non-error completion (dedupe cos>=0.92, min len 40, namespace per active project). src/context/engine.js ContextPlugins.memory does query-aware recall. plugins/memory/handler.js memory tool (add/search/list/forget) is the manual surface over the same store; forget prunes by explicit key only. Legacy memory_local rows migrate via scripts/migrate-memory-to-gm.mjs. test.js gm-learn group + host+tools+toolsets roundtrip witness it (16 groups green). rs-learn.db is WAL so in-process freddie + external gm watcher coexist safely.